abstract: In the last three months, Bernie Sanders raised $25.3 million. Pete Buttigieg raised $19.1 million and Kamala Harris $11.6 million, at a time when donations signal viability.
snippet: In the last three months, Bernie Sanders raised $25.3 million. Pete Buttigieg raised $19.1 million and Kamala Harris $11.6 million, at a time when donations signal viability.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders has produced the biggest fund-raising quarter of the Democratic primary, as his campaign announced on Tuesday that he had taken in $25.3 million over the last three months. Now the big questions looming over the donor race are whether Senator Elizabeth Warren will surpass him, and whether former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. will trail far behind.

headline_main: Sanders Posts Biggest Money Haul of Quarter. Will Warren Top Him?
headline_print_headline: Sanders Posts Biggest Quarter, Adding $25 Million

abstract: The huge infusion of money confirms that President Trump is building an enormous war chest heading into the 2020 election.
snippet: The huge infusion of money confirms that President Trump is building an enormous war chest heading into the 2020 election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s re-election campaign and the Republican National Committee raised a combined $125 million in the last three months, Republican Party officials said on Tuesday, setting a presidential fund-raising record.

headline_main: Trump Campaign and R.N.C. Raise $125 Million in Third Fund-Raising Quarter

abstract: The California senator raised about half of her total funds from digital fund-raising, a campaign spokesman said.
snippet: The California senator raised about half of her total funds from digital fund-raising, a campaign spokesman said.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris of California has raised $11.6 million in the past three months, her campaign said on Tuesday, a total that almost identically matches her fund-raising totals from previous quarters, when she also raised around $12 million.

headline_main: Which 2020 Democrats Raised the Most Money This Summer?

abstract: The large total for his 2020 presidential bid reflected the senator’s continued strength with small-dollar donors.
snippet: The large total for his 2020 presidential bid reflected the senator’s continued strength with small-dollar donors.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders raised $25.3 million in the past three months, his campaign said on Tuesday, a total that continues to demonstrate his strength with small donors as he fights to maintain support in key early-voting states.

headline_main: Bernie Sanders’s Fund-Raising Haul: $25.3 Million in Third Quarter

abstract: The amount is less than what he raised during the previous quarter, when he topped the field in fund-raising with almost $25 million in donations.
snippet: The amount is less than what he raised during the previous quarter, when he topped the field in fund-raising with almost $25 million in donations.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., raised $19.1 million for his presidential campaign during the last three months, his campaign said Tuesday. The figure represents a decrease in his fund-raising pace from earlier in the summer.

headline_main: Tom Steyer: Who He Is and What He Stands For

abstract: The family and classmates of Channing Smith, a high school junior, said his death was a result of “social media bullying” and called for a thorough investigation.
snippet: The family and classmates of Channing Smith, a high school junior, said his death was a result of “social media bullying” and called for a thorough investigation.
lead_paragraph: The family and classmates of a Tennessee high school student who killed himself after being outed online as bisexual have demanded that the school and state authorities investigate and prosecute those responsible, calling it a case of “social media bullying.”
